%N A387539 Sum of the odd parts in the partitions of n into 2 parts.
%H A387539 <a href="/index/Par#part">Index entries for sequences related to partitions</a>
%H A387539 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1, 0, 0, 2, -2, 0, 0, -1, 1).
%F A387539 a(n) = (2*n^2-2*n+1+(2*n-1)*(-1)^n+n*(1+(-1)^n)*(1-(-1)^((2*n-1+(-1)^n)/4)))/8.
%F A387539 a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/2)} k*(k mod 2) + (n-k)*((n-k) mod 2).
%F A387539 a(n) = a(n-1) + 2*a(n-4) - 2*a(n-5) - a(n-8) + a(n-9).
%F A387539 From _Stefano Spezia_, Sep 02 2025: (Start)
%F A387539 G.f.: x^2*(2 - x + 3*x^2 + 4*x^4 - x^5 + x^6)/((1 - x)^3*(1 + x)^2*(1 + x^2)^2).
%F A387539 E.g.f.: ((x - 1)*x*cosh(x) + x*sin(x) + (1 + x)^2*sinh(x))/4. (End)
%e A387539 a(4) = 4, The partitions of 4 into two parts are (3,1) and (2,2) and 1+3 = 4;
%e A387539 a(5) = 4, The partitions of 5 into two parts are (4,1) and (3,2) and 1+3 = 4;
%e A387539 a(6) = 12, (5,1), (4,2), (3,3) and 1+3+3+5 = 12;
%e A387539 a(7) = 9, (6,1), (5,2), (4,3) and 1+3+5 = 9.
%t A387539 Table[Total[Select[Flatten[IntegerPartitions[n, {2}]], OddQ]], {n, 0, 80}]
%t A387539 LinearRecurrence[{1, 0, 0, 2, -2, 0, 0, -1, 1}, {0, 0, 2, 1, 4, 4, 12, 9, 16}, 80]
